        <briefdescription>
<para>LoRa coding rate. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This enumeration defines the LoRa coding rate, used for forward error correction (FEC).</para>
<para>The coding rate is expressed as 4/x, where a lower denominator (e.g., 4/5) means less redundancy, resulting in a higher data rate but reduced robustness. Higher redundancy (e.g., 4/8) improves error tolerance at the cost of data rate. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
