        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="structk__timeout__t" kindref="compound">k_timeout_t</ref></type>
          <declname>timeout</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Perform Channel Activity Detection. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Checks whether a LoRa signal is present on the channel using the modem configuration previously set by <ref refid="group__lora__interface_1gad7c6c516d2d0e023da952666d3f8decb" kindref="member">lora_config</ref> (including CAD parameters).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This is a blocking call.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dev</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>LoRa device </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>timeout</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Maximum time to wait for CAD to complete </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 if no activity detected (channel free) </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>1 if activity detected (channel busy) </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>-EBUSY if the modem is in use </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>-ETIMEDOUT if the operation timed out </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>negative on other errors </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
